Boppin' is an arcade puzzle game for one or two players.  You control 
Yeet and Boik, two characters from an alternate universe video game, who 
must defeat Sweety Hunnybunz, the Singing Treacle Bear and free all the 
video game monsters Hunnybunz has imprisoned.  Yeet and Boik transport from
world to world, throwing blocks to match patterns to free the monsters and
picking up prizes.  The points so accumulated are the energy used to defeat
Hunnybunz at the end in a final battle.

Here are just some of the features of Boppin':

o  3 levels of difficulty, each with 50 worlds for a total of 150 worlds
o  over 2500 tile images
o  All graphics in 32 colors
o  Animated story
o  Multiple endings
o  over 40 sound effects in stereo
o  15 unique pieces of multitrack music
o  two player simultaneous play
o  Second player can start at any time
o  Full-featured editor with online help
o  Easy playing of custom-designed levels
o  Passwords for saving progress in game
o  High score display and save
o  Hard drive installable
o  PAL and NTSC supported

Boppin' requires 1 megabyte of memory and will run on all Amigas.  
Joystick required, mouse recommended for Editor.  Two player option 
requires second joystick.

